vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 6
  }
}
title: |md
  # Mutex vs. Spinlock Decision: Execution Context Matrix
  **Y-Axis**: Can the current execution context sleep?
  **X-Axis**: Does the critical section contain operations that may sleep?
| {
  near: top-center
  style: {
    font-size: 14
    bold: false
    fill: transparent
    stroke: transparent
  }
}
matrix: "" {
  style: {
    fill: transparent
    stroke: transparent
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Column headers в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  col_header_left: "Critical Section:\nMAY SLEEP\n(kmalloc GFP_KERNEL,\ncopy_from_user, etc.)" {
    width: 340
    height: 80
    style: {
      fill: "#E8E8F4"
      stroke: "#9090C0"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: true
      font-size: 14
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  col_header_right: "Critical Section:\nNEVER SLEEPS\n(increment counter,\nbit-flip register, etc.)" {
    width: 340
    height: 80
    style: {
      fill: "#E8F4E8"
      stroke: "#90C090"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: true
      font-size: 14
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Row headers в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  row_header_can_sleep: "Context\nCAN SLEEP\n\n(Process context:\nsyscall handlers,\nwork queues)" {
    width: 160
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#EAF4FF"
      stroke: "#70A0D0"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: true
      font-size: 13
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  row_header_no_sleep: "Context\nCANNOT SLEEP\n\n(Atomic context:\nirq handlers,\nsoftirqs,\nspinlock held)" {
    width: 160
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF4EA"
      stroke: "#D09040"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: true
      font-size: 13
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Q1: can sleep + section may sleep в†’ MUTEX в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  q1: "QUADRANT 1\n\nвњ…  USE MUTEX\n\nmutex_lock_interruptible()\nmutex_unlock()\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nExamples:\nвЂў syscall handler: kmalloc(GFP_KERNEL)\nвЂў syscall handler: copy_from_user()\nвЂў work queue: file I/O\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nM4 Driver в†’ this quadrant:\nmydevice_read()  вЂ” waits for data\nmydevice_write() вЂ” waits for space\nioctl RESIZE     вЂ” kzalloc(GFP_KERNEL)\n\nsizeof(mutex): ~32 bytes\nUncontended lock: ~20вЂ“60 cycles" {
    width: 340
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#D6EAD6"
      stroke: "#40A040"
      stroke-width: 3
      bold: false
      font-size: 12
      border-radius: 8
    }
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Q2: can sleep + section never sleeps в†’ MUTEX preferred в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  q2: "QUADRANT 2\n\nвњ…  MUTEX PREFERRED\n(spinlock also correct)\n\nmutex_lock_interruptible()\n  вЂ” or вЂ”\nspin_lock_irqsave()\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nExamples:\nвЂў syscall handler: atomic_inc(counter)\nвЂў syscall handler: update linked list\n  (no allocation needed)\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nPrefer mutex: allows signals to\ninterrupt the wait, avoids\npriority inversion.\n\nPrefer spinlock only if:\ncritical section is < ~10 cycles\nAND no contention expected." {
    width: 340
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#EAF4D6"
      stroke: "#80B040"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: false
      font-size: 12
      border-radius: 8
    }
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Q3: cannot sleep + section never sleeps в†’ SPINLOCK в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  q3: "QUADRANT 3\n\nвњ…  USE SPINLOCK\n\nspin_lock_irqsave(&lock, flags)\nspin_unlock_irqrestore(&lock, flags)\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nExamples:\nвЂў IRQ handler: update hardware reg\nвЂў softirq: enqueue sk_buff\nвЂў IRQ handler: flip a status bit\nвЂў timer callback: update stats\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nCritical rules:\nвЂў Hold for NANOSECONDS only\nвЂў Never call any function\n  that could sleep\nвЂў Disable interrupts during lock\n\nsizeof(spinlock): 4 bytes\nUncontended: ~5вЂ“15 cycles" {
    width: 340
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF3D6"
      stroke: "#D0A040"
      stroke-width: 2
      bold: false
      font-size: 12
      border-radius: 8
    }
  }
  # в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Q4: cannot sleep + section may sleep в†’ ILLEGAL в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  q4: "QUADRANT 4\n\nрџљ«  ILLEGAL\nKernel BUG() / panic\n\nIF ATTEMPTED:\nspin_lock() then\nkmalloc(GFP_KERNEL)  в†ђ BUG!\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nWhy this explodes:\n1. Spinlock disables preemption\n2. kmalloc(GFP_KERNEL) may sleep\n   to reclaim pages\n3. Trying to sleep with preemption\n   disabled в†’ kernel BUG()\n4. Machine halts or panics\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nKernel detection:\n\"BUG: sleeping function called\nfrom invalid context\"\n\nFix: use GFP_ATOMIC (no sleep)\nor restructure to avoid allocation\ninside atomic context." {
    width: 340
    height: 280
    style: {
      fill: "#FFD6D6"
      stroke: "#C04040"
      stroke-width: 4
      bold: false
      font-size: 12
      border-radius: 8
    }
  }
}
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Legend в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
legend: |md
  **Legend**
  - вњ… **GREEN**: Safe and correct choice
  - вњ… **YELLOW-GREEN**: Correct, choose based on contention profile
  - вњ… **YELLOW**: Safe for atomic contexts only
  - рџљ« **RED**: ILLEGAL вЂ” triggers kernel BUG() / panic
  **M4 Driver Analysis**: All `file_operations` handlers run in **process (syscall) context**
  в†’ execution context **CAN sleep** в†’ top row в†’ **mutex is always correct**.
  `mydevice_read()` and `mydevice_write()` call `copy_to/from_user()` (may fault/sleep)
  and `wait_event_interruptible()` (explicitly sleeps) в†’ **Q1: MUTEX required**.
| {
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#F5F5FF"
    stroke: "#9090C0"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-size: 12
    border-radius: 8
  }
}
